    "text": "Yes/No Questions"
  },
  {
    "_id": "yes_no_questions_intro",
    "__lessons": ["yes or no questions"],
    "__order": 2,
    "__type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Yes/No questions are questions you answer with \"Yes\" or \"No.\" Two common ways to make these quesions are with the verb \"to be\" (am / is / are) and the verb do (do / does).",
    "__forced_pronunciation": "Yes or No questions are questions you answer with \"yes\" or \"no\". Two common ways to make these quesions are with the verb \"to be\" (am / is / are) and the verb do (do / does)."
  },
  {
    "_id": "yes_no_questions_be_header",
    "__lessons": ["yes or no questions"],
    "__order": 3,
    "__type": "subheader",
    "text": "Questions with \"To Be\" "
  },
  {
    "_id": "yes_no_questions_be_carousel",
    "__lessons": ["yes or no questions"],
